## List items [/lists/{listid}/items{?apikey,limit,offset,append_to_response,filter_title,filter_genre,genre_operator,sort,order,unified,released_from,released_to,filter_score_min,filter_score_max}]

#### ðŸ“„ Pagination

Fetches items from a specified list. You can enhance the response by appending additional details like genres and posters using `append_to_response=genre,poster`.

> **Note:** This endpoint returns up to 1,000 items max, regardless of the `limit` value. Use `limit` and `offset` to page through results.
> The response also includes an `X-Has-More` header set to `true` if more items are available beyond the current page.

To filter the results by genre(s), use the `filter_genre` parameter.

> **Note:** When filtering by multiple genres, `genre_operator` controls the logic:
> - **or** (default): matches items with *any* specified genres.
> - **and**: matches items with *all* specified genres.

#### â­ Supporter Feature: Rating Filters

Supporters can filter items by rating thresholds using `_min` and `_max` parameters for any of these rating sources:
- `filter_score_min` / `filter_score_max` - MDBList score (0-100)
- `filter_imdbrating_min` / `filter_imdbrating_max` - IMDb rating (0-100)
- `filter_tmdbrating_min` / `filter_tmdbrating_max` - TMDb rating (0-100)
- `filter_metarating_min` / `filter_metarating_max` - Metacritic rating (0-100)
- `filter_tomatorating_min` / `filter_tomatorating_max` - Rotten Tomatoes rating (0-100)
- `filter_letterrating_min` / `filter_letterrating_max` - Letterboxd rating (0-100)
- `filter_popcornrating_min` / `filter_popcornrating_max` - RT Audience (Popcorn) rating (0-100)
- `filter_malrating_min` / `filter_malrating_max` - MyAnimeList rating (0-100)

**How rating filters work:**
All rating filters use a normalized 0â€“100 scale for consistency across different sources. This allows ratings from different platforms (IMDb, Letterboxd, Metacritic, etc.) to be compared, filtered, and sorted using a single unified scale.

When filtering, always use values between 0 and 100, regardless of the original rating scale.

Multiple rating filters can be combined. Example: `?filter_imdbrating_min=70&filter_tmdbrating_min=75`

By default, items are sorted by rank ascending.


+ Parameters
    + listid: 1176 (integer, required) - The ID of the list.
    + limit: 100 (integer, optional)
    + offset: 10 (integer, optional)
    + append_to_response: `genre,poster` (string, optional) - Additional information to append.
    + filter_title: Matrix (string, optional) - Filter by title.
    + filter_genre: `fantasy` (string, optional) - Filter by genre.
    + genre_operator: `or` (string, optional) - Logical operator used to combine multiple genre filters. Defaults to or.
        + Members
            + `or`
            + `and`
    + released_from: `2020-01-15` (string, optional) - Filter by minimum release date. Format: YYYY-MM-DD.
    + released_to: `2023-12-31` (string, optional) - Filter by maximum release date. Format: YYYY-MM-DD.
    + filter_score_min: 70 (integer, optional) - â­ Supporter only. Filter by minimum MDBList score (0-100).
    + filter_score_max: 90 (integer, optional) - â­ Supporter only. Filter by maximum MDBList score (0-100).
    + sort: `score` (string, optional)
        + Members
